Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.99,0:00:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.49,0:00:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.89,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.54,0:01:44.14,Song,,0,0,0,,How many months have passed away from home? {Kuni o detekara ikutsuki zo} {https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zt9mlcLNjBE&t=3s&ab_channel=Ace.HiromichiKato%E6%92%83%E5%A2%9C%E7%8E%8B%E5%8A%A0%E8%97%A4%E5%BC%98%E9%81%93}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.14,0:01:48.68,Song,,0,0,0,,Ready to face the same fate with the horse, {Tomo ni shinu ki de kono uma to}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.68,0:01:53.08,Song,,0,0,0,,Attacking and conquering mountains and rivers {Semete susunda yama ya kawa}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.08,0:01:57.57,Song,,0,0,0,,Blood flows through the reins I took up {Totta tazuna ni chi ga kayou}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:02:02.12,Song,,0,0,0,,In a pillbox we captured yesterday, {Kino otoshita tochika de}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.12,0:02:06.58,Song,,0,0,0,,we are snoring loudly today {Kyo wa karine no takaibiki}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:10.92,Song,,0,0,0,,My dear horse, did you sleep soundly? {Uma yo gussuri nemuretaka}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.92,0:02:15.09,Song,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's fight will be tough {Asu no ikusa wa tegowaizo}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.83,0:02:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,With its lyrics filled with love for a horse during wartime
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and a playful melody, this song \Nwas warmly received by the masses. {loving to sing (a song); singing with great fondness}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.54,0:02:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It would fall to the creator of these lyrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.85,0:02:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General of the Japanese army \NKuribayashi Tadamichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.39,0:02:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to send the world quivering in their boots \Nduring the battle of Iwo Jima.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Located a measly 690 nautical miles from Tokyo, this island \Nis the southernmost of the Ogasawara Island Chain.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.40,0:02:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As the name implies, \Nit was originally only used as a sulfur (Iwo) mine.
