Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.70,0:02:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,On June 8th, 1944,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.10,0:02:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General Kuribayashi \Nwas appointed the 109th Division commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.74,0:02:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,tasked with organizing the desperate defense of this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.42,0:03:01.41,Sign,,0,0,230,,{\blur1\bord0\b1\c&HFDF5FB&}Episode 23 \N{\fs150}Battle of Iwo Jima
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to be working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.08,0:03:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Never before had the Japanese army known an officer \Nwho'd shake hands with subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.15,0:03:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,During his time in the US and Canada as a military attaché, \NLieutenant General Kuribayashi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.57,0:03:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,learned to be quite a dandy, and was in this regard a unique officer in the otherwise excessively formal Japanese army. {dandy; fop; esthete}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,May we go on a tour through the island at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.53,0:03:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.26,0:03:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The airfield right in front of us is the Chidori Airfield. \NFurther in the distance, in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.47,0:03:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Motoyama Airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From the west, there's Mt. Osaka, Mt. Moto, and Mt. Tamana. Mt. Moto is the northernmost border of the island. {can't find the tamana one}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The longest point from the foot of Mt. Moto over there \Nis Mt. Suribachi in the south, in 8.3 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That narrow gorge near Chidorigahara is only 800 m. {actually "narrow/tight" place}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. This place is a tough nut to crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the enemy wants it badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.33,0:04:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To them, it's like an unsinkable aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it's a perfect springboard \Nfor launching air raids on Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.17,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Air raids on Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be long before they start doing that, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, the US Army leveled \Nthe Marshall and Caroline Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And was now poised for a strike on Saipan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the fall of Saipan, it was only natural to expect a US attack on Iwo Jima next, which offers an air base,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,laying twice as close to the Tokyo Metropolitan Area. {lit: midway to the tokyo ... ; so I think "directly on the way" also fits}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.74,0:04:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It being just a matter of time was apparent \Nto Lieutenant General Kuribayashi all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.19,0:04:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, can we look at the next installation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:04:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Salute! {nc, believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.85,0:05:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing any rivers at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The island has no freshwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.77,0:05:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No freshwater? But how...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainwater is all we got.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We collect it during squalls for later use.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.53,0:05:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, you'd expect to find the \N109th Division Commander Lieutenant General Kuribayashi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Ogasawara Island Chain headquarters on the nearby Chichijima, where it'd be easier to contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.75,0:05:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,However, having seen through the inevitable \NAmerican invasion of Iwo Jima, {this nirami again, still not sure how "glare; sharp look" translates to "seen through"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he decided to personally take command \Nof the defending army.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,During the next week, Lieutenant General Kuribayashi \Ntoured the entire island with inspections.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The flat landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Caves cut in sulfur.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.09,0:06:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, a humid jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.87,0:06:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, American bombers and fighters \Nkept showering Saipan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in bombs and machine gun fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.80,0:07:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwo Jima was almost entirely flat, the only exception the 169 m high Mt. Suribachi in the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of flat terrain makes for a good airfield, but when it comes under attack, it's ridiculously difficult to defend.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.48,0:07:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuribayashi's plan was to build an underground base,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(547,1034)}Mt. Suribachi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(649,824)}Chidori Airfield
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(600,576)} Mt. Moto Airfield
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(1035,530)}Mt. Tamana
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(644,350)}Mt. Osaka
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(899,378)}Northern Airfield
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(885,244)}Mt. Ama {tbh no clue what it is, can't find it in any map}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&H3D87A4&\pos(813,534)}Mt. Byoubu {same, 屏風山}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&HDABF9F&\pos(1154,360)}East Coast
