Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)\blur1\bord3\c&H0C1F20&\3c&HDABF9F&\pos(870,733)}South Coast
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.71,0:07:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,from which they'd wage a guerrilla campaign, \Ndevastating the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They settled on a depth of 30 meters \Nto construct this underground base on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.47,0:07:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This large space on the 3rd underground floor is the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.88,0:07:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And these will be used \Nfor communication between pillboxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.38,0:07:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The total length is expected to be about 25 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly like your idea, but I really don't think \Nyou should go {\i1}that{\i0} deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point building a shelter \Nthat can't withstand a 250 kg bomb hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the geothermal activity is high under this island, \Nwith a lot of sulfur dioxide emissions. {there's no such thing as sulfur gas so maybe write "sulfur dioxide"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, as we were digging a well, just 10 meters \Ninto the ground, it was already 45 degrees hot
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rubber sole on the soldiers' shoes started melting. {... working underground ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.07,0:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, because of all the poisonous gases, \Nwe couldn't work for longer than 5 minutes on end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Exactly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.79,0:08:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwo Jima is probably the most unsuitable place on earth \Nfor any kind of underground works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we'll do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Once Saipan falls to the enemy, \Nthey'll rush full speed to here and Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in particular, because we stand exactly midway \Nbetween Saipan and Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd want it at any cost \Nfor raiding our mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to protect our mainland, \Nwe can't stop at anything, however hard it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.12,0:08:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, help me achieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:09:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's worse, all the construction work \Nhad to be done manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.39,0:09:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.06,0:09:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.15,0:09:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They could only work for 3 to 5 minutes at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying there any longer was too unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the construction progressed steadily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, the pillbox is too exposed. \NYou'd better dump more sand here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.16,0:10:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.72,0:10:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Those enemy planes. They're not here just to scout. \NThey're always taking pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.77,0:10:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if they see a pillbox here, and a trench there, \Nthey'll mark those as targets in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.90,0:10:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the camouflage is so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Air raid! Enemy plane coming! \NReport to your stations! {trusting HA, nc whats sencho haishite}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, Lieutenant General Kuribayashi \Nwrote a letter to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will be brief. \NI'm sure all of you are the same as when I left you. {lit is "I don't think anyone has changed." which probably refers to his family, but at the same time he would totally know his two children grew up, since I've read his letters to children as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing fine so far, \Nthough one can hardly lead a life more hellish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy air raids are becoming an everyday routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.79,0:11:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, they'll land on the island in force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The defenders are all unwavering \Nin their resolve to gain glory in death. {tragic but brave; heroic; grim}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, so am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.35,0:12:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, we're all just weak humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When standing face-to-face with death, \Nhis family is the one thing on everyone's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.58,0:12:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, please keep yourself safe \Nand live for as long as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful to you \Nfor propping me up through all these years. {nc what he means by "thanks for serving me for a long time"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.19,0:12:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Above all, take good care of the children for me."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.08,0:12:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Though he told them he's prepared for the worst, \Nthe reality of Iwo Jima was even direr than that. {no clue what he means:状況は覚悟の上とはいえ、イオウ島はあまりにもひどかった / said about resolve for the acute situation, iwojima was too bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With this letter, he made it clear to his family \Nthat his bones would be buried here on the island.
